Start Trending Salesforce Reports

To trend data in CRM Analytics, you trend a report that's collecting that data.

Required Editions and User Permissions
Available in Salesforce Classic and Lightning Experience.
Available with CRM Analytics, which is available for an extra cost in Enterprise, Performance, and Unlimited Editions. Also available in Developer Edition.

User Permissions Needed
Use CRM Analytics OR Use CRM Analytics Templated Apps
AND
Trend Report Data in CRM Analytics

Create a dataset.
Choose A Salesforce Report from the available data sources.
Select a report.
Enter a title for the trending dashboard and the new trending dataset.
Set a schedule for updating the dashboard.
Choose a different app if you don’t want to save the trending dataset in My Private App.

Click Start Trending.
When the new trending dashboard is ready, you receive an email with a link. After the dashboard is ready, you can also begin to explore the associated dataset, which appears in the CRM Analytics datasets list.

You can’t re-create a trended report. Therefore, it's recommended that you make a copy of the report to guard against data loss.
You can also trend any report directly by clicking Trend on that report.
